                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'Is the application for a search warrant required to be made on oath?', 'yes_no', '{"correct":true,"justification":"Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing"}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *- by sworn information*. (2) Such application shall be by the information on oath and in writing in the Form [34.13](https://www.courts.ie/acc/alfresco/75ad4659-d859-47aa-bbfc-5d582d2c2a7f/Information For Search Warrant - Broadcasting Act, 1990 section 14 No. 34.13.docx/docx/1), Schedule of the member of the Garda Síochána seeking the grant of the warrant.'),
                                                                                                                 ('District – Order 34 - Miscellaneous Search Warrants', 'Court Rules', 'Can an application for a warrant under section 787 of the Companies Act 2014 be made at any sitting of the relevant court district?', 'yes_no', '{"correct":true,"justification":"An application for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 787 of the [Companies Act 2014] may be made at any sitting of the Court for the court district wherein the premises in respect of which the warrant is sought are situated."}'::jsonb, ARRAY['AI', 'Court Rules'], '#### *- venue.* 7.[4] (1) An application for the issue of a warrant pursuant to section 787 of the [Companies Act 2014](https://www.irishstatutebook.ie/eli/2014/act/38/enacted/en/html) may be made at any sitting of the Court for the court district wherein the premises in respect of which the warrant is sought are situated.'),
